ce:section.ce:para:
In this study, crystal violet, a N-rich compound with a symmetrical, propeller-like structure surrounded by a rotating benzene ring (shown in 
                        Figure S1
                     ), was used as a precursor for the preparation of CDs. Considering that sulfuric acid can be used as an acid and doped with S in the process of preparing CDs, the probability of obtaining multi-colour emission fluorescent CDs increased further.Therefore, multi-colour emission fluorescent AIE-CDs were prepared using a water solution with an appropriate amount of sulfuric acid (by controlling the strength of the sulfuric acid) as the reaction solvent at an appropriate reaction temperature and reaction time.The effect of the amount of sulfuric acid, reaction temperature, and reaction time on the structure, functional group characteristics, and fluorescent properties of the prepared-AIE-CDs was studied systematically. Transmission electron microscopy (TEM), Fourier-transform infrared spectroscopy (FT-IR), X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy (XPS), ultraviolet spectroscopy (UV–vis), and fluorescence analyses were used to characterise the properties of AIE-CDs. To illustrate the AIE properties of the CDs, the fluorescence properties of the progressively diluted CDs solutions were studied. Finally, to understand the application value of AIE-CDs, anti-counterfeiting, information encryption, and cell imaging of the prepared-AIE-CDs were performed.
